{"description":"Stories are being collapsed even when the corresponding collapse setting is false/unchecked.

This matches the original bug report: 'an article was collapsed / hidden, but option in Settings not marked'

The issue is likely in the collapse decision logic in check-domain.ts or how the config is being read at the time of story processing.","title":"Stories collapsing independently of settings"}

{"description":"When unchecking a collapse checkbox (e.g., Right Bias), stories that were already collapsed do not uncollapse.

This is likely related to smb-iy0 - if stories are being collapsed incorrectly in the first place, they won't respond correctly to setting changes.

The toggleStoriesByBias() method may not be finding the story elements correctly, or the collapse state is being set incorrectly during initial story processing.","title":"Stories don't uncollapse when setting changes to false"}

